Thoughts on vision?
Felines and canines have the ability to see with lower light level than humans, may extend into the UV range, and have acuity evolved for hunting.
Using those two as examples, an anthro with vision identical to the source would have a difficult time in a visually-oriented human world.
On the other hand, given time and natural selection I believe the spectrum range would eventually include some red/green vision. Better acuity would occur since they'd be sentient and tool users as well.
If you have reptile anthros, replace UV with infrared. I can imagine outdoor signage that absorbs heat from the day and uses that to highlight text.

Perception is fun.

I don't want to have a name attached to whatever I do, in any capacity. I write in part because I just want to have the writing just be, without being attached to anything before or after. There's two choices, either post everything at once, which wasn't what I wanted to do for this, or post the update sections as their own links. For the latter, either you have a bunch of now redundant links cluttering up the archives of a incomplete story, or they're set on a timer that deletes the pastebin posts after X amount of time (because why leave up small and incomplete parts of a now complete narrative?), leaving a bunch of now dead links in its wake.
I've come across the latter enough that I actively don't want to do that, and I don't want to be a namefag and have any sort of account tied to anything I post at all. Meaning I'm at where I am now.
